Quote: <i>Clianthus</i> ... scientic name for an Australasian genus of plants, N.O. <i>Leguminosa,</i> containing only two species-in Australia, <i>Sturt's Desert Pea</i> (q.v.), <i>C. damperi</i>; and in New Zealand, the <i>Kaka-bill </i>(q.v.), <i>C. puniceus.</i> Both species are called <i>glory-pea</i>, from Grk.
